------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party dependencies and their licenses
------------------------------------------------------------------------

This project depends, at runtime or optionally, on the following
third-party packages. sketchpolicy does not vendor or redistribute their
source; they are installed from their own distributions by pip. Their
licenses are reproduced/linked by their respective projects.

Core (required):
  - numpy            BSD-3-Clause
  - scipy            BSD-3-Clause
  - pyarrow          Apache-2.0

Optional extra [ingest] (experimental "sketch" hand-video adapter):
  - mediapipe              Apache-2.0   (Google MediaPipe Hands, 21 landmarks)
  - opencv-python-headless Apache-2.0
  - av (PyAV)              BSD-3-Clause

Optional extra [replay] (read-only kinematic sanity visualization):
  - pybullet         zlib

Optional extra [lerobot] (live-reader cross-verification only):
  - lerobot-dataset  Apache-2.0
    NOTE: this extra pulls a heavy torch + CUDA stack and is NOT required
    for the core demonstration-multiplier path, which writes the
    LeRobotDataset v3.0 format directly via pyarrow.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Explicitly NOT used
------------------------------------------------------------------------
sketchpolicy deliberately does NOT depend on MANO, HaMeR, or WiLoR.
Those projects carry non-commercial / research-only licenses (MANO) or
require GPU ViT inference (HaMeR, WiLoR), which are incompatible with
this project's MIT distribution and CPU-only design goal.
Hand pose, where used, comes solely from MediaPipe Hands (Apache-2.0).
